Hunter Stephen Heburn will remain in custody until the judgment. He allegedly shot and killed a man after he mistook him for a warthog. LIMPOPO - The case against a Limpopo hunter who shot and killed a man after he allegedly mistook him for a warthog concluded his bail application on Tuesday. Police say the judgment for the application will be heard on Friday.Hunter Stephen Heburn will remain in custody until the judgment.The police's Motlafela Mojapelo said: On Friday we will hear whether the suspect is granted bail or not. As the police, we are opposed to bail.&quot;(Edited by Refilwe Thobega)